    <h1 class="header-title" style="text-align: right">How the model works</h1>

    <hr>

    <p style="text-align: right">The data is taken from existing datasets belonging to the NCEI (National Centers for Environmental Information), 
    whose project titled the IBTrACS (International Best Track Archive for Climate Stewardship) recorded <br> cyclone data in all ocean basins. Given that Vanuatu is main
    priority, the West and South Pacific Ocean datasets were the only ones utilised in this model. <br> <br> This cyclone prediction model takes in the relevant readings 
    which is formatted into both input (mixed data) and validation (correct data) sets, which is then analysed and processed by a neural network to constantly <br> generate
    results that closely resemble the validation set; further understanding the right parameters of a cyclone. <br> <br>

    A colour-grade system is displayed for users to easily interpret the magnitude of each statistical feature:</p>

